From my perspective, the hand is a bit weak for 2@C. For 2@C bid I like to have a 9 trick hand. In ben's case you can count 3.5 spades, 1 H, 1C, and 1.25 diamonds or so.  Far less than a 9 trick hand. With his hand, I would just open 1@S. However, let me take the auction as it went. |
