Preheat the oven to 475 degrees.  Cut 10 small openings on both sides of the brisket.  Insert the garlic slices in the cuts in the brisket.  Sprinkle Lawry salt on both sides of the brisket.  Put in roasting pan (it's good to have the brisket hug the sides of the pan).  Place in oven for 20 minutes.

While brisket is browning, slice the onions.  After 20 minutes, remove the brisket from the pan, add a little water and deglaze the pan (get the drippings off the sides into the water for au jus).  Add onions, and put brisket on other side to brown.|
