^d@e@2After 15 minutes, lower oven to 325.  Again deglaze the pot and add a cup of water.  Cover and @E@3cook for 2 more hours.  Be sure to check periodically to make sure there is plenty of liquid.

When the brisket is tender -- remove and pour gravy out.  Again deglaze the pot.  The gravy should be rich (not watery) -- if need be put on stove and reduce.  

Do NOT cut the brisket until it is cold.  Cut off all fat. Then cut into thin slices (AGAINST the grain or it will be stringy).  Get fat off gravy.

Put cut brisket in gravy, and reheat.  

Yum!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!

It's a really simple recipe -- with very few ingredients and always a huge success.


